-----------------------------------------------------------------------
Stratego/XT 0.17 - released April 2008
-----------------------------------------------------------------------

---------++!! Summary of Changes

%TOC%

---------++ Stratego Compiler

* No more nested functions

* Stack traces

   * [STR-311] - strc-lib : a library for compilation (meta-programming) Stratego
   * [STR-548] - .meta file should allow option for not imploding concrete object syntax
   * [STR-613] - Stratego library: Allow creation of library for specific standard (C99, POSIX, POSIX XSI)
   * [STR-697] - Standalone strc; allow users to override --cc and ---ld
   * [STR-723] - Implement pretty-printing support for rules( := ) and rules( :+= ) syntax

---------++ Stratego Language

* Import aterm from file

* Improved embedding of languages (no more layout problems)

   * [STR-751] - Do not export imported constructors from library
   * [STR-550] - Assignment operator
   * [STR-577] - Stratego: support import of an ATerm from a file
   * [STR-501] - Generate chain-f and bigchain-f for dynamic rule f
   * [STR-653] - new operator: an Ensure-Seq operator

---------++ Stratego Libraries

   * [STR-571] - Distribute stratego-libraries for deploying Stratego/XT applications without Stratego/XT

* libstratego-lib

   * [STR-512] - Option handling: support initial actions
   * [STR-513] - Option handling: support check actions
   * [STR-521] - Library: add if-statistics2 etc
   * [STR-604] - newname: _ should be configurable
   * [STR-630] - mod only supports integers, introdce mod for floats

* libstratego-sglr

   * [STR-547] - libstratego-sglr: strategy to set parse tree format is not implemented
   * [STR-446] - Stratego bindings for libsglr
   * [STR-625] - libstratego-sglr: support for start symbols that are not context-free.
   * [STR-632] - libstratego-sglr: support adding position information to AsFix trees.
   * [STR-641] - Move asfix-yield into libstratego-sglr
   * [STR-659] - sdf2ast-conflicts: support numbered priorities
   * [STR-709] - sdf ast attributes: support annotations in ast patterns

* libstratego-gpp


   * [STR-642] - Pretty-print table compiler
   * [STR-503] - Introduce libgpp, providing ast2abox and abox2text as a library
   * [STR-470] - Initiate abox2text unit test suite
   * [STR-570] - pp-aterm: use libstratego-gpp
   * [STR-631] - pp-aterm should be available as (or in) a library

* libstratego-rtg

   * [STR-572] - Introduce libstratego-rtg, providing format checking as a library
   * [STR-675] - format-check: support more complex tree patterns in the right-hand sides

* libstratego-aterm

* libstratego-tool-doc

   * [STR-629] - Introduce libtool-doc, using libstratego-gpp

---------++ ATerm

* ATerm 2.5

* Fixes aterm aliasing problems for GCC 4.x

---------++ SDF

* New SDF2 Bundle

   * [STR-661] - sdf2-bundle generation: include info about the revisions, versions, and URLs of the included packages

- Fixes gcc optimization bugs at x86-64
- Fixes sed issues in GNU Make 3.81

* Argument-specific priorities

* New feature: . priorities.

* Case-insensitive keywords

* No prod-fun

* No unquoted literals

* Dynamic libraries

* More efficient installation of sdf2-bundle thanks to linking against
uninstalled libraries

   * [STR-708] - parse-unit: support annotations in expected and actual results
   * [STR-605] - gen-sdf-mix: Ctx parameter should be hygienic
   * [STR-568] - implode-asfix: allow literal injections.
   * [STR-552] - ast attributes: support single placeholder
   * [STR-110] - Implement an SDF to LaTeX tool for usage in alltt.
   * [STR-355] - parse-unit: support heuristic filter (option?) specification in testsuite
   * [STR-357] - parse-unit: allow testing inputs that are ambiguous.
   * [STR-451] - parse-unit: support matching of variable number of arguments.
   * [STR-452] - parse-unit: use libsglri
   * [STR-419] - gen-renamed-sdf-module: do not rename LAYOUT non-terminals

(Meta-Environment and Martin Bravenboer)

---------++ Performance

---------+++ Format-checking

* DFTA (rtg2dfta)

* Normalized RTG (rtg-normalize)

---------++ Deployment

Native Microsoft Windows using MinGW

Stratego Libraries, C99, POSIX, POSIX+XSI

Mac OS X installer

x86-64

   * [STR-698] - x86_64 support
   * [STR-616] - autoxt: add configure option to disable xtc registration
   * [STR-573] - autoxt: make XTC registration optional
   * [STR-495] - strategoxt rpms should be build using rpms for that specific distribution
   * [STR-362] - autoxt: support target specific STRCFLAGS (foo_STRCFLAGS)

